                  "file_data": null,
                  "function_call": null,
                  "function_response": null,
                  "inline_data": null,
                  "text": "To turn on the parking brake on a Bombardier Challenger 605, follow these steps:\n\n1.  **Depress Brake Pedals:** Fully depress both brake pedals on either the pilot’s or copilot’s side.\n2.  **Pull Handle:** Pull the **PARKING BRAKE** handle.\n3.  **Lock Handle:** Rotate the handle **90°** to the locked position.\n\n### Verification and System Details:\n*   **Confirmation:** A **PARKING BRAKE ON** advisory message will appear on the EICAS to indicate normal engagement.\n*   **Important Note:** Both the inboard and outboard brakes will hold when hydraulic systems 2 and 3 are pressurized. If the hydraulic systems are turned off, only the inboard brakes will hold for a prolonged period.\n*   **Warning:** If the parking brake is engaged while the aircraft is in takeoff mode, a **PARKING BRAKE** warning message will display and a \"CONFIG BRAKE\" aural warning will sound.\n\n### References:\n*   **Document:** CL605-LANDING_GEAR.pdf\n*   **Page:** 15\n*   **Figures:** \n    *   **Figure 15-10-9: Parking Brake** (Shows the location and operation)\n    *   **Figure 15-10-10: PARKING BRAKE Handle** (Detailed view of the handle)\n\nTo release the parking brake, fully depress both brake pedals, rotate the handle back to the unlocked position, and push it down (Page 15).",
